}\pard \sl-355 \tx50 \tqr \tx2421 \fs24 \f0 {\pard \posx2122 \posy3131 \phpg \pvpg \absh-1900 \absw7375 \dxfrtext200 \fs10 \f0 \fs25 \f0 \pard \s4 \posx2122 \posy3131 \phpg \pvpg \absh-1900 \absw7375 \dxfrtext200 \qj \li50 \ri50 \sl-264 \tx50 \tqr \tx7324 The C128 mode is, in effect, a brand new computer inside the Commodore 128. What improvements does this mode offer over the C64 mode? We've already mentioned two areas where the Commodore 64 needed improve\-ment: the slow disk access, and the lack of an 80\_column screen display. The C128 mode eliminates both problems, offering both much faster disk access and the choice\'97with the push of a button\'97of either 80\_column or 40\_column color displays.\par 
}\pard \sl-264 \tx50 \tqr \tx7324 \fs24 \f0 {\pard \posx2141 \posy5333 \phpg \pvpg \absh-2046 \absw7354 \dxfrtext200 \fs10 \f0 \fs30 \f0 \i \pard \s5 \posx2141 \posy5333 \phpg \pvpg \absh-2046 \absw7354 \dxfrtext200 \li52 \ri3768 \sl-319 \tx52 \tqr \tx3585 Disk Data Transfer Speed\par 
\fs10 \f0 \fs25 \f0 \plain \fs25 \lang1033 \pard \s6 \posx2141 \posy5333 \phpg \pvpg \absh-2046 \absw7354 \dxfrtext200 \qj \li50 \ri50 \sl-265 \tx50 \tqr \tx7303 Data transfer times using the disk have been increased more than five times. This is possible using an entirely new family of accessory drives for the C128. These new drives are called the Commodore 1571 and 1572. The 1571 (shown with other peripherals in Figure 1\_3) is a single drive, and the 1572 is a dual\_drive unit. These drives will be discussed in more detail in the chapter on peripherals.\par 
